<h1>Maple Balsamic Brussels Sprouts</h1>
<h2>Servings: 4</h2>
<h3>Source: https://www.mydarlingvegan.com/maple-balsamic-brussels-sprouts-with-hazelnuts-and-rosemary/</h3>

<h4>Ingredients</h4>
<ul>
<li>4 cups Brussels sprouts, halved</li>
<li>2 tablespoons olive oil</li>
<li>1/2 red onion, thinly sliced</li>
<li>2-3 garlic cloves, minced</li>
<li>salt and pepper, to taste</li>
<li>3 tablespoons balsamic vinegar</li>
<li>2 teaspoon maple syrup</li>
</ul>

<h4>Directions</h4>
<ol>
<li>1. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F.</li>
<li>2. Wash and half the Brussels Sprouts and toss them with oil, onions, garlic, salt, and pepper. Spread onto a baking sheet in a single layer and bake for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until browned on the outside and tender on the inside.</li>
<li>3. Stir together balsamic vinegar and maple syrup and set aside.</li>
<li>4. Remove from oven and toss with maple balsamic glaze.</li>
</ol>

